{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.13",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 13,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 13",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 13 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.13.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:1",
      "text": "Lo, mine eye hath seen all this, mine ear hath heard and understood it.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.13.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:2",
      "text": "What ye know, the same do I know also: I am not inferior unto you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.13.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:3",
      "text": "Surely I would speak to the Almighty, and I desire to reason with God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.13.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:4",
      "text": "But ye are forgers of lies, ye are all physicians of no value.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.13.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:5",
      "text": "O that ye would altogether hold your peace! and it should be your wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.13.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:6",
      "text": "Hear now my reasoning, and hearken to the pleadings of my lips.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.13.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:7",
      "text": "Will ye speak wickedly for God? and talk deceitfully for him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.13.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:8",
      "text": "Will ye accept his person? will ye contend for God?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.13.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:9",
      "text": "Is it good that he should search you out? or as one man mocketh another, do ye so mock him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.13.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:10",
      "text": "He will surely reprove you, if ye do secretly accept persons.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.13.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:11",
      "text": "Shall not his excellency make you afraid? and his dread fall upon you?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.13.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:12",
      "text": "Your remembrances are like unto ashes, your bodies to bodies of clay.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.13.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:13",
      "text": "Hold your peace, let me alone, that I may speak, and let come on me what will.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.13.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:14",
      "text": "Wherefore do I take my flesh in my teeth, and put my life in mine hand?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.13.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:15",
      "text": "Though he slay me, yet will I trust in him: but I will maintain mine own ways before him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.13.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:16",
      "text": "He also shall be my salvation: for an hypocrite shall not come before him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.13.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:17",
      "text": "Hear diligently my speech, and my declaration with your ears.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.13.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:18",
      "text": "Behold now, I have ordered my cause; I know that I shall be justified.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.13.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:19",
      "text": "Who is he that will plead with me? for now, if I hold my tongue, I shall give up the ghost.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.13.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:20",
      "text": "Only do not two things unto me: then will I not hide myself from thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.13.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:21",
      "text": "Withdraw thine hand far from me: and let not thy dread make me afraid.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.13.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:22",
      "text": "Then call thou, and I will answer: or let me speak, and answer thou me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.13.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:23",
      "text": "How many are mine iniquities and sins? make me to know my transgression and my sin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.13.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:24",
      "text": "Wherefore hidest thou thy face, and holdest me for thine enemy?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.13.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:25",
      "text": "Wilt thou break a leaf driven to and fro? and wilt thou pursue the dry stubble?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.13.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:26",
      "text": "For thou writest bitter things against me, and makest me to possess the iniquities of my youth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.13.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:27",
      "text": "Thou puttest my feet also in the stocks, and lookest narrowly unto all my paths; thou settest a print upon the heels of my feet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.13.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:28",
      "text": "And he, as a rotten thing, consumeth, as a garment that is moth eaten.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
